text.tspan: significant number of students also sought support from friends and engaged in self-soothing
practices like yoga, diary writing, or meditation (Table 10). However, comparatively fewer
sought support from adults. Due to the lockdown, several students expressed that they could not
play outdoor sports or hang out with friends, preventing them from engaging in coping activities.
They also expressed signs of anxiety due to a drastic change in their daily routines. However,
while some students reported increased quality time with family members as a stress buster,
others expressed "unnecessary interaction with family members" to cause more stress. A student
wrote, "I used to talk with my teachers in the coaching classes face to face and share my grief.
But now, as we can't leave our homes, that is not possible" (Participant 62). This statement points
to the fact that although tuition classes themselves place additional stress on students, the tutors
may be more friendly and understanding than school teachers.
